# From https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/edt/
# Not vendored as its own file: `edt` uses the exact same
# `{?X a ?D} <= {?C rdfs:subClassOf ?D. ?X a ?C}` backward subClassOf rule as
# `deep-taxonomy` (see deep_taxonomy.n3 above), just over a differently-named
# 10000-level chain (30002 rdfs:subClassOf triples in test-dl.ttl) -- i.e. a
# duplicate scalability benchmark of the same feature at a size unsuitable
# for a fast conformance test. Skipped as redundant; see deep_taxonomy.n3 for
# the (truncated) case that actually runs.
